    "recap_text": "YPSILANTI, Mich. -\nThe Akron Zips got a boost from f\nKelton Phillips\n, who totaled three hits in a 6-2 loss to the Eastern Michigan Eagles Sunday.\nIn addition to his three hits, Phillips had a double and two RBI\u00a0to lead the Zips.\nAustin Lafferty\nfurnished a noteworthy performance at the plate as well, going 1-for-2 with a double.\nTrieg Matthews\n(2-1) got the ball to start for Akron (10-12, ) and took the loss.\nLandon Vandegrift\nwas a bright spot for the Zips, coming out of the bullpen and throwing one shutout inning, allowing one hit.\nHOW IT HAPPENED\nThe Zips got on the scoreboard first, starting in the third inning. Akron scored twice on a two-run double off the bat of Phillips. The Zips were unable to hold the lead, as Eastern Michigan scored six times over the remaining six innings to grab the 6-2 win.\nGAME NOTES\n\u00bb Phillips led the Zips, picking up three base knocks in the ballgame.\n\u00bb Akron's highest scoring inning was the third, when it pushed two runs across.\n\u00bb Akron pitchers faced 42 Eastern Michigan hitters in the game, allowing 12 ground balls and six fly balls while striking out six.\n\u00bb Phillips led the Zips at the plate, going 3 for 3 with a double and two RBI.\nWHAT'S NEXT?\nAkron stays on the road as it travels to Mercyhurst on Tuesday, March 24, for a 2 p.m. start.",
